"""
This function gives the complex refractive index of glass. Since there too many kind of glasses, we set constant values of 1.52 for the refractive index and 0 for the extinction coefficient. for infrared region this might not be true, so you can check "Dispersion relations" in http://www.cvilaser.com/PublicPages/Pages/TechnicalTips.aspx
Usage: Nc = glass(λ)
Input: λ:   wavelength
Output: n:  complex refractive index, filled with zeros in the imaginary part
author: lnacquaroli
"""
function glass(λ::AbstractArray{T,M}) where {T<:Number, M}
    N = ones.(length(λ)) .* (1.52 + im * 0)
end # EOF glass(...)

